This paper deals with computer-assisted diagnosis using medical imaging datasets, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for data augmentation, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method involves the use of bounding box annotations, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE) and object detection (cs.CV). Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which is a sub-field of multimedia (cs.MM).
